<div id="review_3543773" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3543773" />
    <a title="Tara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47239-tara"><img alt="Tara" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1402817283p2/47239.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3543773?book_show_action=true">Jul 26, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tara" href="/user/show/47239-tara">Tara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">oversexed and underaged pseudo-history buffs</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/47239-tara?shelf=junk">junk</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3543773" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14270587621169355861">I would rather like my two hours back that I spent on this book. It&apos;s not that it was bad, rather, it had an intriguing premise, but the past/future aspects were poorly merged, the part of the story set in present day was absolutely unsatisfying and the Georgian smut felt out of place, perhaps because of the highly formal nature she tried to give the characters.<br/><br/>The lesson to be learned there is you can&apos;t do Pride and Prejudice with an R rating.</span>
  <span id="freeText14270587621169355861" style="display:none">I would rather like my two hours back that I spent on this book. It's not that it was bad, rather, it had an intriguing premise, but the past/future aspects were poorly merged, the part of the story set in present day was absolutely unsatisfying and the Georgian smut felt out of place, perhaps because of the highly formal nature she tried to give the characters.<br /><br />The lesson to be learned there is you can't do Pride and Prejudice with an R rating.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14270587621169355861" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
