    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer198877241" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8979968646411082146">The first in Lauren Willig&apos;s <i>Pink Carnation</i> series. I found this gem in the library. My first by this author and coincidentally the author&apos;s first. I was pleasantly pleased with it. I wasn&apos;t sure I would be when I opened the first page. I&apos;m not a fan of 1st person POV but I kept on and realized the whole book is not written that way and I came to enjoy the parts that were. This is one of those stories in a story. It starts with a young American woman seeking information for her dissertation on s</span>
  <span id="freeText8979968646411082146" style="display:none">The first in Lauren Willig's <i>Pink Carnation</i> series. I found this gem in the library. My first by this author and coincidentally the author's first. I was pleasantly pleased with it. I wasn't sure I would be when I opened the first page. I'm not a fan of 1st person POV but I kept on and realized the whole book is not written that way and I came to enjoy the parts that were. This is one of those stories in a story. It starts with a young American woman seeking information for her dissertation on some English spies from Napoleon's time. She is granted access to papers that has her uncovering the identity of the Pink Carnation. I will be rushing back to the library and seeing if they have the next in the series and crying if they don't.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8979968646411082146" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


